'''General Secretary of the Central Committee''' ({{lang-km|លេខាបក្សកុំមុយនីសកម្ពុជា}}) was the highest office in the [[Communist Party of Kampuchea]].<ref>http://www.camnet.com.kh/cambodia.daily/selected_features/textbook.htm</ref> The [[General Secretary]] was elected at [[plenary session]]s of the Party's [[Central Committee]], and chaired the Secretariat and [[Politburo]]. The office was abolished when the CPK dissolved in 1981, two years after being removed from power in a [[Vietnamese invasion of Cambodia|counterattack by Vietnamese forces]].
