The '''Inter Tribal Council''' (ITC) is a Brazilian [[indigenous peoples]] [[NGO]] founded in 1991. They believe that the first step to fighting discrimination is to ensure access to peoples' rights to health, education, opportunity and cultural dialogue as well as their rights to their lands. They participated in the drafting of [[UN]] initiatives on indigenous peoples inclusion in the information society. {{citation needed|date=December 2008}} They also organized the Jogos dos Povos Indígenas, or [[Indigenous Peoples' Games]], in [[Brazil]], the parallel Indigenous Social Forum,<ref>{{cite web| title=Começam Jogos dos Povos Indígenas em Porto Nacional| accessdate=2015-06-08| date=2011-05-11| publisher=Conexao Tocantins| language=Portuguese| url=http://conexaoto.com.br/2011/11/05/comecam-jogos-dos-povos-indigenas-em-porto-nacional}}</ref> and the first [[World Indigenous Games]], to be held in Brazil in 2015.<ref>{{cite web| title=Statement by International Chief Wilton Littlechild, I.P.C.| accessdate=2015-06-08| url=http://papersmart.unmeetings.org/media2/3346066/win-6.pdf}}</ref> They participated in the [[Convention on Biological Diversity|Convention on Biological Diversity COP 8 Conference]] in [[Curitiba]], Brazil,<ref>{{cite web| title=Convention on Biological Diversity| publisher=UNEP| accessdate=2015-06-08| url=http://www.cbd.int/doc/meetings/cop/cop-08/information/cop-08-inf-48-en.pdf}}</ref> and in 2006 they participated in the I Regional Conference of the Americas against Racism and Racial Discrimination and against All Forms of Discrimination and Intolerance in [[Brasilia]].{{citation needed|date=December 2008}}

