'''Potassium adipate''' is a [[Compound (chemistry)|compound]] with formula K<sub>2</sub>C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O<sub>4</sub>. It is the [[potassium]] [[salt (chemistry)|salt]] of [[adipic acid]].

It has [[E number]] "E357".

